http://purl.org/dc/elements/1.1/title.value: Alabama Course of Study: Health Education

http://purl.org/dc/terms/description.value: The 2009 Alabama Course of Study: Health Education provides the framework for the health education program in Alabama's public schools. Content standards and related content included in bullets in this document are minimum and required (Code of Alabama, 1975, §16-35-4). They are fundamental and specific but not exhaustive. In developing local curriculum, school systems may include additional content standards to reflect local philosophies and add implementation guidelines, resources, and activities; which, by design, are not contained in this document.
Consumer and Community Health
Name major health care professions.

http://purl.org/ASN/schema/core/comment.value: Examples: nurse, dentist, physician, pharmacist

http://purl.org/dc/terms/description.value: Identify health information sources in the community.

http://purl.org/ASN/schema/core/comment.value: Examples: parents, school nurse, family doctor

http://purl.org/dc/terms/description.value: Recognize health-enhancing activities that promote clean schools, homes, and communities.

http://purl.org/ASN/schema/core/comment.value: Example: participating in school-wide cleanup, Auntie Litter, and People Against a Littered State (PALS) projects

http://purl.org/dc/terms/description.value: Recognize safety instructions on consumer products.

http://purl.org/ASN/schema/core/comment.value: Examples: telephone, Internet, television, digital video diskette (DVD)

http://purl.org/dc/terms/description.value: Identify roles and responsibilities of health care professionals within the community.

http://purl.org/ASN/schema/core/comment.value: Examples: police and fire departments, emergency medical services (EMS)

http://purl.org/dc/terms/description.value: Explain the importance of warnings found on tobacco products and medical and chemical containers.
Recognize media messages affecting consumer health decisions.

http://purl.org/ASN/schema/core/comment.value: Examples: cost, safety, effectiveness, side effects

http://purl.org/dc/terms/description.value: Compare health-related resources regarding reliability.

http://purl.org/ASN/schema/core/comment.value: Example: comparing health information in professional journals to health information in tabloid magazines

http://purl.org/dc/terms/description.value: Compare name brand to generic health care products.

http://purl.org/ASN/schema/core/comment.value: Examples: county health departments, American Red Cross, American Diabetes Association

http://purl.org/dc/terms/description.value: Explain cultural influences on health behaviors, including social norms, family traditions, and stereotypes.

http://purl.org/ASN/schema/core/comment.value: Example: family eating habits

http://purl.org/dc/terms/description.value: Identify procedures for making consumer health complaints.

http://purl.org/ASN/schema/core/comment.value: Examples: speaking with a store manager, calling the Better Business Bureau, contacting a patient-relations representative

http://purl.org/dc/terms/description.value: Describe health advocacy strategies.

http://purl.org/ASN/schema/core/comment.value: Examples: writing and recording public service announcements for school or community broadcasts, writing letters to editors of local newspapers, implementing a school health improvement project

http://purl.org/dc/terms/description.value: Analyze technology for its influence on consumer health and health care.

http://purl.org/dc/terms/description.value: Describe practices that protect the environment and control disease.

http://purl.org/dc/terms/description.value: Describe how health is affected by the environment.

http://purl.org/dc/terms/description.value: Describe ways to advocate for a healthy environment
Describe global environmental issues.

http://purl.org/ASN/schema/core/comment.value: Examples: family perceptions of health care professionals, family perceptions of healthy body image, societal expectations of remaining abstinent until married

http://purl.org/dc/terms/description.value: Identify personal, financial, and legal responsibilities of parenthood
Identifying negative consequences associated with teen parenthood

http://purl.org/dc/terms/description.value: Personal Health and Safety

http://purl.org/ASN/schema/core/comment.value: Examples: school—staying seated on the bus, observing playground rules home—using the Internet with parental supervision, establishing emergency escape routes community—staying close to parent in a mall, practicing water safety

http://purl.org/dc/terms/description.value: Describe the importance of personal hygiene health habits related to puberty and adolescence.

http://purl.org/ASN/schema/core/comment.value: Examples: use of alcohol, tobacco, and other drugs; premarital sexual activity; selfmutilation

http://purl.org/dc/terms/description.value: Recognize basic first aid skills.

http://purl.org/ASN/schema/core/comment.value: Examples: washing wounds with soap and water; applying the Rest, Ice, Compression, Elevation (RICE) technique to injured muscles or joints

http://purl.org/ASN/schema/core/comment.value: Example: three C's—Check the scene, Call 911, Care for victim

http://purl.org/dc/terms/description.value: Propose strategies for self-defense, including parking lot safety, Internet safety, and telephone safety.

http://purl.org/ASN/schema/core/comment.value: Examples: wearing protective gear, using seat belts, handling flammable materials properly

http://purl.org/dc/terms/description.value: Describe personal responsibility for reducing hazards and avoiding accidents.

http://purl.org/ASN/schema/core/comment.value: Examples: birth or death of a loved one, marriage, childbirth, adoption, divorce, illness, victimization, relocation, end-of-relationship
